limitations.

128
00:17:22,107 --> 00:17:25,565
Stable diseases aren't lethal.

129
00:17:25,644 --> 00:17:28,636
Deadly ones burn out
too quickly.

130
00:17:28,714 --> 00:17:33,208
Mother Nature can only be fooled
so much.

131
00:17:33,285 --> 00:17:34,752
Deploy my weapon,

132
00:17:34,820 --> 00:17:37,721
and your enemies--
however great--

133
00:17:37,790 --> 00:17:39,951
will collapse from within.

134
00:17:45,030 --> 00:17:48,522
Rather like Mr. Monza
is collapsing right now.

135
00:17:57,976 --> 00:18:00,001
What the hell is going on?

136
00:18:00,079 --> 00:18:02,411
Monza told Ml6
about this meeting.

137
00:18:02,481 --> 00:18:04,847
That's why the change
of location.

138
00:18:04,917 --> 00:18:07,317
He was going to turn
me over to them

139
00:18:07,386 --> 00:18:09,616
and then seek
asylum in the West.

140
00:18:12,424 --> 00:18:15,416
A smart man would have
known I was on to him.

141
00:18:15,494 --> 00:18:18,088
He would never have
got on the plane.

142
00:18:18,163 --> 00:18:19,994
But I knew you would, Mr. Monza,

143
00:18:20,065 --> 00:18:22,863
because you actually
thought you could fool me.

144
00:18:27,673 --> 00:18:29,937
That, gentlemen,

145
00:18:30,008 --> 00:18:32,738
is the sound
of a traitor dying.

146
00:18:42,354 --> 00:18:44,379
