Ya!

179
00:21:19,111 --> 00:21:20,271
Bryce! What have we got?

180
00:21:20,379 --> 00:21:22,142
Well, I haven't even finished
loading the images

181
00:21:22,214 --> 00:21:23,408
from your camera yet.

182
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:30,083
What about references to an orb?

183
00:21:30,155 --> 00:21:32,123
I took the liberty of checking.

184
00:21:32,190 --> 00:21:33,748
Historical inventories
of the Luna Temple

185
00:21:33,825 --> 00:21:34,757
do not list any orb.

186
00:21:34,826 --> 00:21:36,623
Then I want you both to list

187
00:21:36,695 --> 00:21:39,391
every orb ever mentioned
in Greek history.

188
00:21:39,464 --> 00:21:40,624
Every one?

189
00:21:40,699 --> 00:21:41,688
Ha!

190
00:21:46,371 --> 00:21:47,929
Ah...

191
00:21:50,842 --> 00:21:51,274
Ya!

192
00:21:51,343 --> 00:21:52,207
That's...

193
00:21:52,277 --> 00:21:54,268
Iiable...

194
00:21:54,346 --> 00:21:55,370
to be...

195
00:21:59,384 --> 00:22:00,612
...thousands.

196
00:22:04,156 --> 00:22:06,624
Then we'll read thousands.

197
00:22:08,627 --> 00:22:10,652
Start with that one.

198
00:23:05,650 --> 00:23:09,142
Perhaps you gentlemen would
like some tea while you wait?

199
00:23:09,221 --> 00:23:10,654
No, they wouldn't.

200
00:23:10,722 --> 00:23:13,520
Tea is for guests.
The door is for intruders.

201
00:23:15,093 --> 00:23:17,425
Lara, these men are from Ml6.

202
00:23:17,496 --> 00:23:18,520
Yes, I can tell

203
00:23:18,597 --> 00:23:20,895
from their soft hands
and pressed suits

204
00:23:20,966 --> 00:23:22,866
that these are the men
who make decisions

205
00:23:22,934 --> 00:23:23,901
and leave the dirty
work for others.

206
00:23:23,969 --> 00:23:25,698
I have no interest in...

207
00:23:25,771 --> 00:23:27,204
His name's Chen Lo.

208
00:23:27,272 --> 00:23:28,830
Along with his brother Xien,

209
00:23:28,907 --> 00:23:32,240
he runs a ring of Chinese
bandits known as the Shay-Ling.

210
00:23:32,310 --> 00:23:33,436
They deal in guns,

211
00:23:33,512 --> 00:23:35,275
diamonds, antiquities,
anything that Chen Lo

212
00:23:35,347 --> 00:23:37,110
can sell on the black market.

213
00:23:37,182 --> 00:23:39,776
They followed you from the
moment you arrived in Santorini,

214
00:23:39,851 --> 00:23:42,046
where they killed your friend,
Gus, and sank his boat.

215
00:23:42,120 --> 00:23:43,052
Why?

216
00:23:43,121 --> 00:23:44,179
For this.

217
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:46,281
After you were
picked up at sea,

218
00:23:46,425 --> 00:23:48,689
our listening post in Malta
intercepted that fax.

219
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:52,457
It was sent from Chen Lo
to a man named Jonathan Reiss.

220
00:23:52,531 --> 00:23:55,295
What, the scientist?
Won the Nobel Prize.

221
00:23:55,367 --> 00:23:56,629
He's now
the foremost designer

222
00:23:56,701 --> 00:23:58,225
of biological weapons
in the world.

223
00:23:58,303 --> 00:23:59,861
His creations have been
at the heart

224
00:23:59,938 --> 00:24:02,634
of every act of bioterror
in the past 1 5 years.

225
00:24:02,707 --> 00:24:05,437
Reiss's disdain
for life is legendary.

226
00:24:05,510 --> 00:24:07,034
He has no political agenda.

227
00:24:07,112 --> 00:24:09,546
He doesn't care
who his weapons kill, or why.

228
00:24:11,550 --> 00:24:14,041
A modern-day Dr. Mengele.

229
00:24:18,256 --> 00:24:20,588
We know Chen Lo followed you
in order to obtain the orb,

230
00:24:20,659 --> 00:24:22,456
but we also know that
he'll deliver Reiss.

231
00:24:22,527 --> 00:24:24,017
What we don't know is why.

232
00:24:24,095 --> 00:24:25,756
Candidly, that terrifies us.

233
00:24:25,831 --> 00:24:28,629
Reiss is not to be trifled with.

234
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:30,793
Pandora's box.

235
00:24:34,339 --> 00:24:37,399
Reiss is going to use the orb
to find Pandora's box.

236
00:24:38,777 --> 00:24:40,267
Do you mean the Greek myth?

237
00:24:40,345 --> 00:24:43,143
Pandora's given a box by God,
told not to open it.

238
00:24:43,215 --> 00:24:45,615
She does and unleashes
pain into the world?

239
00:24:45,684 --> 00:24:49,085
That's the Sunday school
version, yes.

240
00:24:49,154 --> 00:24:51,145
How do you think life began?

241
00:24:51,223 --> 00:24:53,487
Shooting star,
primordial ooze?

242
00:24:54,659 --> 00:24:56,957
In 2300 BC,
an Egyptian pharaoh

243
00:24:57,028 --> 00:24:59,019
found a place that he named

244
00:24:59,097 --> 00:25:02,624
the Cradle of Life,
where we, life, began.

245
00:25:02,701 --> 00:25:04,999
And there, he found a box,

246
00:25:05,070 --> 00:25:06,594
the box which brought
life to Earth.

247
00:25:06,671 --> 00:25:08,161
The pharaoh opened the box,

248
00:25:08,240 --> 00:25:10,936
but all that was left inside
was the Ramante, or anti-life.

249
00:25:11,009 --> 00:25:12,806
The plague which came as
the companion

250
00:25:12,878 --> 00:25:14,038
to life.

251
00:25:14,112 --> 00:25:15,079
Companion?

252
00:25:15,146 --> 00:25:16,943
Nature is about balance.

253
00:25:17,015 --> 00:25:18,243
All the world comes in pairs.

254
00:25:18,350 --> 00:25:20,648
Yin and Yang.
Right and wrong. Men and women.

255
00:25:20,719 --> 00:25:21,743
What's pleasure without pain?

256
00:25:21,820 --> 00:25:23,014
What did this plague do?

257
00:25:23,088 --> 00:25:25,022
It leveled the pharaoh's army.

258
00:25:25,090 --> 00:25:28,116
The pharaoh's son dispatched
his finest soldier

259
00:25:28,193 --> 00:25:31,424
to take the box and transport it
to the end of the world.

260
00:25:34,165 --> 00:25:37,498
2,000 years later, Alexander
the Great reached lndia,

261
00:25:37,569 --> 00:25:39,833
where his army was ravaged

262
00:25:39,905 --> 00:25:41,702
by a plague,
after one of his men

263
00:25:41,773 --> 00:25:43,502
found a box among some remains.

264
00:25:43,575 --> 00:25:46,271
India? That's where
the pharaoh's man brought it?

265
00:25:46,411 --> 00:25:49,141
Mmm. Alexander felt
that the box was too powerful

266
00:25:49,214 --> 00:25:50,613
to be trusted to any man,

267
00:25:50,682 --> 00:25:53,583
so he returned it to its home
in the Cradle of Life.

268
00:25:54,819 --> 00:25:57,253
And it has never
been seen since.

269
00:25:57,322 --> 00:25:59,790
And this... Cradle of Life
is where?

270
00:25:59,858 --> 00:26:01,189
No one knows.

271
00:26:01,259 --> 00:26:03,591
Alexander found it using
a map that was with the box.

272
00:26:03,662 --> 00:26:05,960
A map he then hid
from the world.

273
00:26:06,031 --> 00:26:08,795
But the name he gave
this map was Mati.

274
00:26:08,867 --> 00:26:13,031
And the literal translation
for the word "Mati" is "eye."

275
00:26:14,506 --> 00:26:15,734
The orb is the map,

276
00:26:15,807 --> 00:26:18,435
hidden in the Luna Temple
by Alexander.

277
00:26:18,510 --> 00:26:21,502
And Reiss will use it
to find Pandora's box.

278
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:23,980
And when he does,
when he opens it,

279
00:26:24,049 --> 00:26:25,983
he will unleash a weapon
more powerful

280
00:26:26,051 --> 00:26:27,575
than you could ever imagine.

281
00:26:31,790 --> 00:26:35,055
The markings definitely form
a pattern, but...

282
00:26:35,126 --> 00:26:36,889
even if I figure out
what they represent,

283
00:26:36,962 --> 00:26:38,429
we still can't read
the whole map,

284
00:26:38,496 --> 00:26:40,794
because... we've only got
a partial view of it, you see?

285
00:26:40,865 --> 00:26:43,265
Well, we have to figure out
how to read it.

286
00:26:43,368 --> 00:26:45,836
Right. Thank you.

287
00:26:45,904 --> 00:26:47,132
On behalf of Her Majesty,

288
00:26:47,205 --> 00:26:48,797
we formally request
that you find

289
00:26:48,873 --> 00:26:50,773
and recover this box
before Dr. Reiss.

290
00:26:50,842 --> 00:26:52,275
Oh!

291
00:26:52,410 --> 00:26:55,038
Well, now that I have
Her Majesty's permission...

292
00:26:55,113 --> 00:26:57,809
Tell me where
to find the orb.

293
00:26:57,882 --> 00:27:00,316
Last we heard, it was
somewhere in China

294
00:27:00,385 --> 00:27:01,511
with Chen Lo
and the Shay-Ling.

295
00:27:01,586 --> 00:27:03,076
Finding them will be
next to impossible,

296
00:27:03,154 --> 00:27:04,985
but we'll assign two
of our best agents to help.

297
00:27:05,056 --> 00:27:07,217
I don't want them.

298
00:27:07,292 --> 00:27:09,089
With all due respect, expertise
in archaeology doesn't...

299
00:27:09,160 --> 00:27:11,151
I didn't say that
I don't need help,

300
00:27:11,229 --> 00:27:13,060
but your agents
will never get me

301
00:27:13,131 --> 00:27:14,189
to Chen Lo in time.

302
00:27:14,265 --> 00:27:16,631
I need an insider,
someone who knows

303
00:27:16,701 --> 00:27:17,963
the Shay-Ling.

304
00:27:18,036 --> 00:27:20,937
Their methods, their hideouts.

305
00:27:23,074 --> 00:27:24,701
I need Terry Sheridan.

306
00:27:24,776 --> 00:27:25,834
Not in a million years.

307
00:27:25,910 --> 00:27:27,707
Not if he were the
last man on Earth.

308
00:27:29,547 --> 00:27:31,913
Terry Sheridan--
formerly a commander

309
00:27:31,983 --> 00:27:35,475
with the Royal Marines,
turned mercenary and traitor.

310
00:27:35,553 --> 00:27:37,077
You don't honestly expect me

311
00:27:37,155 --> 00:27:39,248
to put that man on the trail
of a weapon

312
00:27:39,391 --> 00:27:42,292
he can turn around and sell
to the highest bidder?

313
00:27:57,308 --> 00:27:58,400
Open.

314
00:28:00,278 --> 00:28:01,472
I am your host...

315
00:28:01,546 --> 00:28:03,138
Armin Kal.

316
00:28:03,214 --> 00:28:05,648
Welcome to Fantasy lsland.

317
00:28:57,135 --> 00:28:59,262
Croft.

318
00:28:59,337 --> 00:29:02,067
Hello, Terry.

319
00:29:09,314 --> 00:29:11,179
So, what do you think
of my new place?

320
00:29:11,249 --> 00:29:14,013
It's not quite Croft Manor.

321
00:29:16,121 --> 00:29:18,089
What? A key to your heart?

322
00:29:18,156 --> 00:29:20,784
To a flat in Zurich.

323
00:29:22,694 --> 00:29:24,753
You can pick another city,
if you want.

324
00:29:24,829 --> 00:29:26,592
Your record will be expunged,

325
00:29:26,664 --> 00:29:27,688
your citizenship restored.

326
00:29:27,766 --> 00:29:28,698
By?

327
00:29:28,767 --> 00:29:29,699
Ml6.

328
00:29:29,768 --> 00:29:30,735
Ml6.

329
00:29:30,802 --> 00:29:33,202
Now, would that make me Faust...

330
00:29:33,271 --> 00:29:34,932
or the Devil?

331
00:29:35,006 --> 00:29:36,234
Well,
you can pick one,

332
00:29:36,341 --> 00:29:38,935
because Ml6 will also arrange
a new identity.

333
00:29:39,010 --> 00:29:41,240
Oh, yeah?
You think I need their help?

334
00:29:41,346 --> 00:29:43,814
Oh, having two faces
doesn't count.

335
00:29:45,950 --> 00:29:48,441
So, what do I have to do?

336
00:29:48,520 --> 00:29:50,249
You need to take me
to the Shay-Ling.

337
00:29:50,321 --> 00:29:51,447
The Shay who?

338
00:29:51,523 --> 00:29:52,922
There's a man named Chen Lo

339
00:29:52,991 --> 00:29:55,516
who took something from me,
and I want it back.

340
00:29:55,593 --> 00:29:56,719
Yeah, now, is that you

341
00:29:56,795 --> 00:29:57,955
or Ml6?

342
00:29:58,029 --> 00:29:59,656
Also, I've arranged
for the government

343
00:29:59,731 --> 00:30:02,063
to wire you five million
in sterling when we succeed.

344
00:30:02,133 --> 00:30:03,065
You can call it

345
00:30:03,134 --> 00:30:04,499
second-chance money.

346
00:30:04,569 --> 00:30:06,434
Or life insurance, for you.

347
00:30:06,504 --> 00:30:08,062
I don't need any.

348
00:30:11,643 --> 00:30:14,077
You and l, working alone?

349
00:30:14,145 --> 00:30:16,841
Well, it's easier
to see through you that way.

350
00:30:16,915 --> 00:30:18,940
So, what if afterwards,

351
00:30:19,017 --> 00:30:22,248
Ml6 decides
that me back in the world

352
00:30:22,320 --> 00:30:24,481
isn't such a great idea?

353
00:30:24,556 --> 00:30:27,957
Then I feel sorry for whomever
they get to come after you.

354
00:30:33,198 --> 00:30:35,291
Do you have authorization
to kill me, Croft?

355
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:38,096
Anytime, for any reason.

356
00:30:38,169 --> 00:30:40,763
So, why don't you
just do it, then?

357
00:30:40,839 --> 00:30:43,137
What is it they say?

358
00:30:43,208 --> 00:30:44,436
"Hell hath no fury."

359
00:30:44,509 --> 00:30:46,170
You're not that good.

360
00:30:46,244 --> 00:30:50,305
The Shay-Ling
are like ghosts, Croft.

361
00:30:50,448 --> 00:30:52,473
They move constantly,

362
00:30:52,550 --> 00:30:54,541
and their home
is the most remote

363
00:30:54,619 --> 00:30:56,211
mountain region in China.

364
00:30:56,287 --> 00:30:57,754
Region?

365
00:30:57,822 --> 00:31:00,382
You'll have to do better
than that.

366
00:31:12,770 --> 00:31:15,034
Get me into China,

367
00:31:15,106 --> 00:31:17,370
and I'll get you
to them in a day.

368
00:31:17,442 --> 00:31:19,808
No guns, no money,

369
00:31:19,878 --> 00:31:21,505
no weapons of any kind.

370
00:31:21,579 --> 00:31:24,480
Talk about taking
the fun out of life.

371
00:31:40,531 --> 00:31:42,431
The Shay-Ling have spies
all over China.

372
00:31:42,500 --> 00:31:44,525
We have to get into
the country undetected.

373
00:31:44,602 --> 00:31:47,298
So, we slip into Beijing,
and we go by truck.

374
00:31:47,405 --> 00:31:48,838
Truck? Hmm.

375
00:31:48,907 --> 00:31:52,673
I was thinking about something
a little faster.

376
00:31:58,316 --> 00:32:00,216
A little faster?

377
00:32:03,421 --> 00:32:04,911
Well, this is a little faster,

378
00:32:04,989 --> 00:32:06,889
but the Chinese
will track the pod.

379
00:32:08,993 --> 00:32:10,927
There won't be any pod to find.

380
00:32:10,995 --> 00:32:12,360
Will there be
any of us to find?

381
00:32:20,638 --> 00:32:22,037
Ready? Now.

382
00:32:22,106 --> 00:32:23,232
Ready for what?

383
00:32:41,793 --> 00:32:44,159
The ditching was good, Croft.

384
00:32:44,228 --> 00:32:45,889
I'll give you that.

385
00:32:45,964 --> 00:32:49,297
But we're never going to find
a vehicle in a place like this.

386
00:32:57,008 --> 00:32:58,737
Oh, it's so lovely to see you.

387
00:33:01,813 --> 00:33:03,007
So, is everything ready?

388
00:33:03,081 --> 00:33:04,013
Yes.

389
00:33:04,082 --> 00:33:05,379
Your clothes, guns

390
00:33:05,450 --> 00:33:07,418
and knives are over there.

391
00:33:07,485 --> 00:33:12,616
And I took the liberty
of tuning your bike.

392
00:33:12,690 --> 00:33:13,622
May l?

393
00:33:13,691 --> 00:33:14,658
Yes.

394
00:33:30,808 --> 00:33:32,969
Lara.

395
00:33:33,044 --> 00:33:35,877
Ah, what is
the happy couple up to?

396
00:33:35,947 --> 00:33:37,039
Accessorizing.

397
00:33:37,115 --> 00:33:39,777
Where are we on reading the orb?

398
00:33:39,851 --> 00:33:42,820
All maps have a key, Lara,
a scale, a legend, yes?

399
00:33:42,887 --> 00:33:44,787
The orb's key,
it's not on the orb.

400
00:33:44,856 --> 00:33:46,050
It must've been lost.

401
00:33:46,124 --> 00:33:47,989
Or is somewhere in the temple.

402
00:33:48,059 --> 00:33:49,993
Go through every image I took.

403
00:33:50,061 --> 00:33:52,154
Start with the ones
near the orb.

404
00:33:52,230 --> 00:33:55,290
The key must have been linked
to it in some way.

405
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:57,834
Right.
Bye, then.

406
00:33:57,902 --> 00:34:00,666
It's unlike Lara
to take a partner.

407
00:34:00,738 --> 00:34:02,706
Where are you two going?

408
00:34:02,774 --> 00:34:05,038
We'll take a nice little trip.

409
00:34:05,109 --> 00:34:08,010
Breathe some fresh mountain air.

410
00:34:08,079 --> 00:34:11,242
Stop by my friends,
the Shay-Ling.

411
00:34:23,995 --> 00:34:25,690
The Shay-Ling watch
all the roads.

412
00:34:25,763 --> 00:34:26,923
We'll have to go

413
00:34:26,998 --> 00:34:28,090
around the back.

414
00:34:28,166 --> 00:34:29,861
We'll go straight.

415
00:34:29,934 --> 00:34:31,595
Maybe you didn't hear me.

416
00:34:31,669 --> 00:34:34,103
The Shay-Ling have
men on every road

417
00:34:34,172 --> 00:34:35,537
from here to Lo Yang.

418
00:34:35,606 --> 00:34:38,598
Not every road.

419
00:35:11,776 --> 00:35:13,038
A bit rusty, are we?

420
00:35:13,111 --> 00:35:14,601
Oh, I think it's coming back.

421
00:35:14,679 --> 00:35:17,477
I expected more from a Scot.

422
00:35:17,548 --> 00:35:19,038
I don't expect anything

423
00:35:19,117 --> 00:35:20,550
from an Englishwoman.

424
00:35:20,618 --> 00:35:22,984
Good, 'cause you're not
going to get anything.

425
00:36:02,193 --> 00:36:04,218
Fun's over.

426
00:36:04,362 --> 00:36:06,159
From now on, it's by foot.

427
00:36:10,001 --> 00:36:12,629
Best to reconsider
that "no gun" rule.

428
00:36:12,703 --> 00:36:14,193
No.

429
00:36:15,740 --> 00:36:17,332
Okay.

430
00:36:25,149 --> 00:36:27,640
And don't be looking at my ass.

431
00:36:29,120 --> 00:36:30,610
So, where do I fit in?

432
00:36:30,688 --> 00:36:32,178
What do you mean?
You're the guide.

433
00:36:32,256 --> 00:36:34,520
I mean, when you think back

434
00:36:34,592 --> 00:36:36,219
on the vast scheme

435
00:36:36,294 --> 00:36:37,886
of your
hugely adventurous life...

436
00:36:37,962 --> 00:36:40,658
where do I fit in?

437
00:36:40,731 --> 00:36:42,255
Was I the love of your life,

438
00:36:42,333 --> 00:36:44,130
or just another bump
on the road?

439
00:36:44,202 --> 00:36:46,067
Was I time well spent?

440
00:36:46,137 --> 00:36:47,729
Four months?

441
00:36:47,805 --> 00:36:51,172
More good than bad?

442
00:36:51,242 --> 00:36:53,870
Come on, it had to be
more than that, am I right?

443
00:36:55,646 --> 00:36:57,580
You're right.

444
00:36:57,648 --> 00:36:59,741
It was five months.

445
00:37:02,486 --> 00:37:04,420
-You're laughing at me.
-No, no.

446
00:37:04,488 --> 00:37:06,217
At the fact,
I used to find you charming.

447
00:37:08,626 --> 00:37:10,184
I am charming.

448
00:37:12,029 --> 00:37:13,394
Hmm.

449
00:37:37,622 --> 00:37:38,987
You're late.

450
00:37:44,161 --> 00:37:45,685
Tilt your head back.

451
00:37:45,763 --> 00:37:47,196
Do it!

452
00:37:51,402 --> 00:37:54,064
You might see again
in an hour. Maybe.

453
00:38:04,982 --> 00:38:06,882
What's this?

454
00:38:06,951 --> 00:38:09,715
It's not there.

455
00:38:09,787 --> 00:38:11,220
There's no orb.

456
00:38:11,355 --> 00:38:14,381
Is there anything
you can tell me about this?

457
00:38:30,341 --> 00:38:31,603
Hello.

458
00:38:31,676 --> 00:38:34,076
I take it you didn't
like your messenger.

459
00:38:34,145 --> 00:38:35,339
I didn't.

460
00:38:35,413 --> 00:38:37,574
But I did like the men
I lost in the temple.

461
00:38:37,648 --> 00:38:40,344
You underestimated
Lady Croft.

462
00:38:40,418 --> 00:38:44,548
I underestimated how much
this orb is worth.

463
00:38:44,622 --> 00:38:47,853
There's so many horrible
diseases in the world...

464
00:38:47,925 --> 00:38:51,190
things we are particularly
susceptible to as children.

465
00:38:51,262 --> 00:38:53,457
You never know
when you could be holding

466
00:38:53,531 --> 00:38:55,260
Iittle Shiho or Tai by the hand

467
00:38:55,366 --> 00:38:58,767
as a mysterious ailment
ravages their bodies.

468
00:38:58,836 --> 00:39:03,830
You kill them, and I will give
your orb to Lady Croft.

469
00:39:03,908 --> 00:39:05,375
My men tell me

470
00:39:05,443 --> 00:39:07,638
she is a few miles away
from here, as we speak.

471
00:39:07,712 --> 00:39:10,306
I wonder how much she would pay.

472
00:39:10,381 --> 00:39:13,441
I'll pay you an additional
12 million dollars.

473
00:39:13,517 --> 00:39:16,111
It will be yours,
once you've delivered

474
00:39:16,187 --> 00:39:19,156
the orb to me,
along with Lady Croft's body.

475
00:39:19,223 --> 00:39:21,214
I don't think you know
where they are.

476
00:39:21,359 --> 00:39:23,190
You're impossible,
you know that?

477
00:39:23,260 --> 00:39:26,821
I think you pretended to know,
so I would get you out.

478
00:39:26,897 --> 00:39:28,023
This isn't a tomb, Croft,

479
00:39:28,099 --> 00:39:29,657
and the Shay-Ling
aren't mummies.

480
00:39:29,734 --> 00:39:31,429
They're killers.

481
00:39:31,502 --> 00:39:34,471
But if you don't trust me...

482
00:39:39,043 --> 00:39:42,877
I'm sorry to have to do this,
but you're wasting time.

483
00:39:46,283 --> 00:39:48,012
You want to shoot me?
Shoot me.

484
00:39:48,085 --> 00:39:51,577
Personally,
I'd rather you do it...

485
00:39:51,655 --> 00:39:52,952
than them.

486
00:40:12,143 --> 00:40:14,111
Well, Terry...

487
00:40:14,178 --> 00:40:16,510
what part of
"Never come back again!"

488
00:40:16,580 --> 00:40:17,740
didn't you understand?

489
00:40:21,752 --> 00:40:23,617
You wanted to find
the Shay-Ling.

490
00:40:25,256 --> 00:40:27,053
Come on!

491
00:40:27,124 --> 00:40:30,457
The only way to get into their
place is as their prisoners.

492
00:40:30,528 --> 00:40:33,292
Ah, you might have told me
that little gem before.

493
00:40:33,431 --> 00:40:35,058
Ah, you would have believed me?

494
00:40:35,132 --> 00:40:37,532
Make Chen Lo a better
offer than his buyer.

495
00:40:37,601 --> 00:40:39,262
He'll cross them.

496
00:40:39,336 --> 00:40:41,463
Even if his buyer
is Jonathan Reiss?

497
00:40:42,807 --> 00:40:45,674
You might have told me
that little gem before.

498
00:41:29,987 --> 00:41:31,852
Were you really
going to kill me?

499
00:41:31,922 --> 00:41:34,948
Oh, I bet she would have.

500
00:41:35,025 --> 00:41:36,720
I have seen her in action.

501
00:41:36,794 --> 00:41:38,261
Didn't Terry tell you?

502
00:41:38,329 --> 00:41:43,232
The last time any of us saw him,
he was riding away with a truck

503
00:41:43,300 --> 00:41:46,599
full of my Ming vases.

504
00:41:46,670 --> 00:41:49,298
And sitting next to him...

505
00:41:49,406 --> 00:41:52,102
was his sister.

506
00:41:54,345 --> 00:41:55,903
Well, how is she?

507
00:41:55,980 --> 00:41:59,541
You... shouldn't
have come here.

508
00:41:59,617 --> 00:42:02,518
It got me out of prison.

509
00:42:02,586 --> 00:42:04,918
Besides, the lady
has a good offer.

510
00:42:04,989 --> 00:42:06,479
Better than Reiss.

511
00:42:06,557 --> 00:42:08,855
Really?

512
00:42:08,926 --> 00:42:10,188
Should I take it?

513
00:42:10,261 --> 00:42:11,751
Take it.

514
00:42:11,829 --> 00:42:13,456
Or, better yet,

515
00:42:13,531 --> 00:42:15,396
you and I ransom
her and the thing

516
00:42:15,466 --> 00:42:17,297
back to the British for triple.

517
00:42:18,702 --> 00:42:20,431
Let's talk.

518
00:42:21,639 --> 00:42:22,731
Not you, Terry.

519
00:42:22,806 --> 00:42:25,832
Lady Croft and l.

520
00:42:25,910 --> 00:42:27,844
You wait here.

521
00:42:29,079 --> 00:42:30,706
Catch up.

522
00:42:30,781 --> 00:42:33,045
I'll be four minutes.

523
00:42:34,552 --> 00:42:35,951
Terrific.

524
00:42:38,589 --> 00:42:39,749
There's something

525
00:42:39,823 --> 00:42:41,154
I think you will appreciate.

526
00:42:51,735 --> 00:42:53,293
This is the largest group

527
00:42:53,437 --> 00:42:55,837
of terra-cotta warriors
I have found.

528
00:42:55,906 --> 00:43:00,002
The King of Chin made them
for use in the afterlife...

529
00:43:00,077 --> 00:43:03,911
to fend off enemies
he made in this one.

530
00:43:03,981 --> 00:43:07,075
Hmm. Sounds like we
could both use a set.

531
00:43:07,151 --> 00:43:10,382
I would be happy
to sell some to you.

532
00:43:10,454 --> 00:43:13,855
I hope you're as entrepreneurial
with the orb.

533
00:43:13,924 --> 00:43:16,620
You lost men, I lost men.

534
00:43:16,694 --> 00:43:19,754
I see no reason
we should both lose again.

