Has it been four minutes yet?

553
00:45:58,689 --> 00:46:01,249
That was nice.

554
00:46:02,593 --> 00:46:07,223
It's too bad
you're on the wrong side.

555
00:46:07,297 --> 00:46:10,926
Tell me where the orb is,
and it spares your life.

556
00:46:13,871 --> 00:46:16,704
The flower pagoda, in Shanghai.

557
00:46:16,774 --> 00:46:18,674
9:00 p.m.

558
00:46:20,310 --> 00:46:22,676
This is mine.

559
00:46:31,522 --> 00:46:34,320
Now we're even.

560
00:46:47,671 --> 00:46:48,638
Now!

561
00:47:07,324 --> 00:47:08,814
Remember that "no gun" rule?

562
00:47:08,892 --> 00:47:11,156
I reconsidered!

563
00:47:43,260 --> 00:47:45,626
I know there's a staircase
we could've used.

564
00:48:00,410 --> 00:48:02,002
I am alone

565
00:48:02,079 --> 00:48:03,979
Then I swore

566
00:48:04,047 --> 00:48:08,609
¡ÓWhen you were
the last... high¡Ó

567
00:48:08,685 --> 00:48:12,621
¡ÓHigh...¡Ó

568
00:48:12,689 --> 00:48:14,520
Lara, are you all right?

569
00:48:14,591 --> 00:48:15,853
Smashing.

570
00:48:15,926 --> 00:48:17,689
I'm on my way to Shanghai,

571
00:48:17,761 --> 00:48:20,525
and I need you to look
at something for me.

572
00:48:20,597 --> 00:48:22,929
It was in the Luna Temple
near the orb.

573
00:48:23,000 --> 00:48:26,800
And I'm betting it's the key
to those markings.

574
00:48:26,870 --> 00:48:29,998
She's holding some sort
of musical instrument.

575
00:48:32,009 --> 00:48:33,977
It's sound.

576
00:48:34,044 --> 00:48:35,875
That's brilliant.

577
00:48:35,946 --> 00:48:37,937
The key must have been linked
to it in some way.

578
00:48:38,015 --> 00:48:38,947
I'll start decoding

579
00:48:39,016 --> 00:48:40,244
-the images we have.
-Good.

580
00:48:40,317 --> 00:48:41,579
You get us the rest.
Bye, Lara.

581
00:48:41,652 --> 00:48:43,950
-Bye.
-Miss you.

582
00:49:53,385 --> 00:49:55,478
Oh, well.

583
00:49:55,553 --> 00:49:57,316
Just like old times.

584
00:50:02,327 --> 00:50:03,919
I think that's the first time

585
00:50:03,995 --> 00:50:07,487
you've actually smiled
because of me.

586
00:50:14,072 --> 00:50:15,699
Why did you do it?

587
00:50:15,774 --> 00:50:18,174
I started thinking.

588
00:50:18,243 --> 00:50:20,939
I was tired of doing things
somebody else's way,

589
00:50:21,012 --> 00:50:23,845
and it was always going
to be somebody else's way.

590
00:50:23,915 --> 00:50:26,816
So, you abandon your men
and betray your country?

591
00:50:26,885 --> 00:50:30,286
Leaving my men and my country,

592
00:50:30,388 --> 00:50:33,516
that didn't actually hurt
as much as I thought.

593
00:50:33,591 --> 00:50:35,491
But leaving you did.

594
00:50:35,560 --> 00:50:38,290
Mm.

595
00:50:38,396 --> 00:50:42,230
You're a hard act to follow,
Croft.

596
00:50:47,105 --> 00:50:50,404
You know why you and I get along
so well?

597
00:50:50,475 --> 00:50:52,170
No.

598
00:50:53,912 --> 00:50:55,812
We are two of a kind,
me and you.

599
00:50:59,684 --> 00:51:01,151
We are nothing alike.

600
00:51:01,219 --> 00:51:04,052
I don't think we're alike,

601
00:51:04,122 --> 00:51:06,249
but I do think we're a pair.

602
00:51:06,391 --> 00:51:10,487
Opposite sides
of the same coin.

603
00:51:33,852 --> 00:51:36,184
My men have the roof covered.

604
00:51:36,254 --> 00:51:39,052
Why don't you set down
in the square instead?

605
00:51:39,124 --> 00:51:41,752
That way, my men will also
have things covered.

606
00:51:41,826 --> 00:51:43,157
Okay, fine.

607
00:51:44,028 --> 00:51:46,087
Okay, Sean, let's go!

608
00:51:49,634 --> 00:51:52,933
They're landing in the square.

609
00:51:53,004 --> 00:51:55,734
We're in the wrong position.

610
00:51:55,807 --> 00:51:56,739
Stairs?

611
00:51:56,808 --> 00:51:57,706
No time.

612
00:51:57,775 --> 00:51:58,707
-Rooftops?
-No.

613
00:51:58,776 --> 00:52:00,744
I've got a plan.

614
00:52:00,812 --> 00:52:01,938
Stay here.

615
00:52:02,013 --> 00:52:04,038
Wait for my signal.

616
00:52:06,351 --> 00:52:08,478
Here's the money!

617
00:52:08,553 --> 00:52:10,043
Come and get it!

618
00:52:18,062 --> 00:52:19,586
Wait for my signal, huh?

619
00:52:19,664 --> 00:52:20,824
Give me that box!

620
00:52:20,899 --> 00:52:22,491
You give me my money first!
Come on!

621
00:52:22,567 --> 00:52:23,795
Give me that box now!

622
00:52:23,868 --> 00:52:25,460
No, just toss it.

623
00:52:25,537 --> 00:52:26,504
You first!

624
00:52:36,381 --> 00:52:37,780
Quick! Get us out of here!

625
00:52:39,684 --> 00:52:41,174
Take us up!

626
00:53:05,577 --> 00:53:07,204
Take it up!

627
00:53:20,558 --> 00:53:22,958
Go! Run her over!

628
00:53:37,875 --> 00:53:39,035
Yeah?

629
00:53:39,110 --> 00:53:40,873
We tried it your way.

630
00:53:40,945 --> 00:53:42,071
Now we do it mine!

631
00:53:42,146 --> 00:53:44,011
Bring it to the top
of the pagoda now!

632
00:53:44,082 --> 00:53:45,572
Okay!

633
00:54:24,722 --> 00:54:26,189
I got you!

634
00:54:36,367 --> 00:54:38,927
Come on! Come on!
Hold it up!

635
00:54:46,477 --> 00:54:49,207
Come closer!
I can't reach it!

636
00:54:49,280 --> 00:54:51,043
Raise it higher!
Higher!

637
00:54:55,019 --> 00:54:56,646
My regards to your brother!

638
00:54:56,721 --> 00:54:58,086
We're too late.

639
00:54:59,791 --> 00:55:02,885
Croft, what are you doing?

640
00:55:13,805 --> 00:55:14,829
Take us up!

641
00:55:19,143 --> 00:55:20,201
Move! Go!

642
00:55:28,019 --> 00:55:29,782
Let's go! Move!

643
00:55:43,267 --> 00:55:45,861
I'm getting tired of you
pointing that thing at me.

644
00:55:45,937 --> 00:55:46,869
Are you okay?

645
00:55:46,938 --> 00:55:48,132
Never better.

646
00:55:48,206 --> 00:55:49,798
Looks like we lost the orb.

647
00:55:51,909 --> 00:55:54,434
Please. You don't think
I'd go vaulting into thin air

648
00:55:54,512 --> 00:55:55,444
for nothing, do you?

649
00:55:55,513 --> 00:55:57,447
I put a tracer on the crate.

650
00:56:00,084 --> 00:56:02,314
Got it. Look.

651
00:56:07,091 --> 00:56:08,786
Impressive.

652
00:56:37,555 --> 00:56:38,579
A weapons lab

653
00:56:38,656 --> 00:56:40,624
in the middle of the city?

654
00:56:40,691 --> 00:56:41,817
No way.

655
00:56:41,893 --> 00:56:44,020
He must've dumped that crate.

656
00:56:44,095 --> 00:56:46,689
No, it's here.

657
00:56:46,764 --> 00:56:49,198
One of the buildings?

658
00:56:49,267 --> 00:56:53,294
No. It's exactly
where we're standing.

659
00:56:59,710 --> 00:57:02,975
There's a part of me that always
allowed for the possibility

660
00:57:03,047 --> 00:57:05,038
that Pandora's box
was just a legend,

661
00:57:05,116 --> 00:57:07,914
but now I know it's there.

662
00:57:13,458 --> 00:57:15,221
She escaped.

663
00:57:15,293 --> 00:57:17,693
She has no idea where we are.

664
00:57:17,762 --> 00:57:19,024
We take no chances.

665
00:57:19,096 --> 00:57:22,532
Have everything we need
to manufacture an antidote

666
00:57:22,600 --> 00:57:24,227
transferred to the jet.

667
00:57:28,039 --> 00:57:30,507
I need an out for two people.

668
00:57:30,575 --> 00:57:33,271
Mid-city. Soon.

669
00:57:34,445 --> 00:57:36,003
What, are you crazy?

670
00:57:39,016 --> 00:57:39,983
Are we set?

671
00:57:40,051 --> 00:57:42,281
Piece of cake.

